allows a campaign to skip the 'press star to confirm' step, also allows for a human check (not answering machine) which actually sucks in practice because it adds a 3 second delay before the intro starts playing

allow conditional printing of debug statements in political_data, campaign for battle-for-the-net, config cleanup.

Call tool can now load a remote Google spreadsheet which overrides default campaign behaviors on a per-state basis. Using this, you can change the order of the house rep senator calls, always call an individual politician first, or add a special name and number to call before any of the politicians. Also we are now able to randomize the campaign phone call order.
pull out campaign parameters into variables from if statement. moving towards allowing specific overrides.
rename randomize campaign param to randomize_order for more clarity
allow randomization of campaigns, always randomize senator call order
